## Analysis of the Main Target Image:

The target image shows a structure with two separate sub-structures. The one on the left is composed of two blocks, and the one on the right is made of seven blocks.

**Left Sub-Structure:**
- Layers: 2
- Blocks: 2
- Spatial Relationships: A red arch block forms the base, and an orange right-triangular prism sits on top of it.

**Right Sub-Structure:**
- Layers: 4
- Blocks: 7
- Spatial Relationships: Two red arch blocks form the base. A yellow rectangular block sits on top of the arches. A green cube sits on top of the yellow block. A blue cube sits next to the green cube. A red arch sits on top of the green and blue cubes. An orange right-triangular prism sits on top of the red arch.
